		  Installation Instructions for Griz4s

			  ** Version 13.1 **

			Updated July 16, 2013


******************************************************************************************
Griz requires Mili version 11.1 or later. The following gnu tools are also
requited:  gmake

Once the Griz tarfile has been extracted, execute the following steps in this order:


(1) cd to the directory GrizDist
    change the date in file misc.h to todays date

(2) Enter the command: 

    ./configure 

    Or, if you need to use a different mili other 
    than the default installation on LC.

    ./configure --with-mili= ** directory

(3) A new directory will be created - it with start with "GRIZ4", 
    for example: GRIZ4-chaos_3_x86_64-YANA/

    cd into this directory

(4) Enter the command: gmake clean; gmake opt; gmake batch_opt;

(5) The Griz execution script called "griz4s" can be found in the directory
    /bin_opt. DO NOT COPY THIS SCRIPT FILE INTO THE MDG SPACE.

(6) To run/test Griz, enter the command:  ./bin_opt/griz4s -i input_file


** Livermore Specific **

(7) To install an executable on the LC machines do the following:
    a). Perform steps 1-5 above
    b). cp bin_opt/griz4s.linux-gnu_opt bin_opt/griz4s.linux_opt
    c). cp bin_batch_opt/griz4s.linux-gnu_opt_batch bin_batch_opt/griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    d). give mdgadmin bin_opt/griz4s.linux_opt bin_batch_opt/griz4s.linux_opt_batch
    e). xsu mdgadmin
    f). cd /collab/usr/apps/mdg/archive/grizdir/[grizalpha|grizbeta|grizversion]/bin
    g). cp griz4s.linux_opt griz4s.linux_opt-MMMDDYYYY
    h). cp griz4s.linux_opt_batch griz4s.linux_opt_batch-MMMDDYYYY
    i). take -f username
    j). Most Important - logout as mdgadmin and run a test using the new installed version

